<item>
            <title>[LU-3357] lctl replace_nids loses Target UUID from llog header</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3357</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is reproducible using master (circa tag 2.4.50)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Prior to replace nids:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[root@lumgr1 CONFIGS]# llog_reader t32fs-client
Header size : 8192
Time : Thu Feb  7 22:24:35 2013
Number of records: 35
Target uuid : config_uuid 
-----------------------
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After remounting w/ nosvc and running:&lt;br/&gt;
lctl replace_nids t32fs-OST0000 192.168.139.20@tcp&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;same log files is now:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Header size : 8192
Time : Mon May 20 09:13:03 2013
Number of records: 35
Target uuid :  
-----------------------
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &quot;Target uuid&quot; is also deleted from t32fs-MDT0000.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I used conf-sanity/32 tarball disk2_1-ldiskfs.tar.bz2 as my starting point.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
