                            <comment id="58977" author="utopiabound" created="Tue, 21 May 2013 14:28:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mike,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This field doesn&apos;t seem to be used too often, but it is checked in the lctl conf_param code path, and if it&apos;s not set correctly, the conf_param fails (see llog_init_handle) in MDS debug_log in &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/8391fe9a-c0cf-11e2-8490-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/8391fe9a-c0cf-11e2-8490-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="58972" author="tappro" created="Tue, 21 May 2013 13:45:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wonder is that so critical to see that UUID? I find it useless, we know already that this is config llog, just because of name. Is it really helpful for something or used by some other tool?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
